spans.text: The loathing maid for his embrace
Where Peace had built her downy nest
Contemplating his ill-spent life , And , cloyed with thefts
nice , None found acceptance in his eyes

over the plains my realms extend
side she walked , Of settlements and jointures talked
To miss her happy fate she tells ; And , of the grand alliance vain , Contemns her kindred of the plain
the noisy hound To scent his footsteps on the ground
